seed_chunks:
Rain makes the city’s alliances look clean until you lean in close. The Halcyon Civic League bankrolls soup lines and “urban renewal,” while quietly buying judges and foreclosing blocks for a private redevelopment map. The Dockside Brotherhood poses as a longshoremen’s union keeping men fed; beneath the ledgers, they run contraband through storm drains and sell muscle to the highest bidder. The Saint Brigid Trust funds hospitals and charity wards, but launders political bribes through endowments and blackmails donors with clinic records. Halcyon hires Brotherhood intimidation to clear tenants; the Trust brokers introductions and cleans the money. Lately the Brotherhood is skimming, and Halcyon wants them buried—preferably with Eli’s name on the shovel.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Halcyon Civic League",
      "public_front": "Philanthropic civic group funding soup lines, scholarships, and urban renewal projects.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Controls courts and city hall via bought judges and quiet debt; engineers foreclosures to assemble entire districts for a private redevelopment scheme."
    },
    {
      "name": "Dockside Brotherhood",
      "public_front": "Longshoremen’s union and mutual-aid society protecting dockworkers’ jobs and pay.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Moves contraband through docks and storm drains; rents out intimidation and enforcement to politicians and developers."
    },
    {
      "name": "Saint Brigid Trust",
      "public_front": "Religious charity trust funding hospitals, clinics, and ward programs for the poor.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Launders bribes through endowments; blackmails donors and officials using clinic records and “confidential” intake files."
    }
  ]
}
```

Rain can’t wash the soot off this week. Halcyon Civic League’s “Renewal Hearing” opens at City Hall, but the judge is already bought and the tenant roll is already forged; Dockside Brotherhood crews are clearing buildings the night before with quiet batons and louder fires. Down in Saint Brigid’s charity ward, a records clerk has gone missing with intake ledgers naming donors, judges, and a certain well-dressed patron—now the Trust is locking down clinics while Halcyon offers “protection.” Eli’s name is circulating as a convenient thief, and Brotherhood spotters are tailing him.

```json
