  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Renewal Hearing",
      "description": "Halcyon Civic League pushes a fast-tracked urban renewal case through City Hall using a bought judge and forged tenant records, while Dockside Brotherhood muscle clears targeted buildings ahead of inspectors via intimidation and staged “accidents.”",
      "tensions": [
        "Tenants disappear or recant under pressure",
        "Arson and beatings spike in the redevelopment blocks",
        "Any investigator near the paper trail becomes a scapegoat"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Saint Brigid Ledger Lockdown",
      "description": "A Saint Brigid Trust clerk vanishes with clinic intake ledgers that can tie donors and officials—including a well-dressed patron—to blackmail and bribes; the Trust seals wards, Halcyon offers security, and the Brotherhood hunts the missing files for leverage.",
      "tensions": [
        "Patients are turned away, sparking unrest and riots",
        "Witnesses are silenced before they can talk",
        "Eli is framed as the thief to draw heat off the real players"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

